description:
Next, we explore the life of the Waldenses in the higher valleys. They fled the lower valleys to avoid persecution, and tried to establish a normal life from then on. However, their normal meant training missionaries, and tutoring the young on how to study and teach the bible in a harsh and unforgiving terrain. Through their well-trained children, younger people, and older people, they impacted the whole continent, spreading the gospel throughout Europe as missionaries ‘disguised’ as students and workers.

To find out more information of the Waldenses check out our extended article.
http://www.lineagejourney.com/reformation/movements/the-waldenses/
